<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-63-1055 </DOCNO><TEXT>Natural gas measurement as we have known is changing. Measurement usedto be considered an art, now it has become a science. Also the naturalgas industry has changed into a more competitive market. Gas distributioncompanies need to know how much gas they are purchasing and selling instantly.The advent of new technology and the need for immediate gas flow informationhas fostered the use of microelectronics by gas distribution companies.This paper addresses the use of real time measurement equipment and howit is being integrated into a gas distribution system.</TEXT></DOC>